div.div:
- Usually only DoIP edge node responds to External test equipment and internal nodes shall not be visible externally (i.e. edge node as a firewall to prevents direct access from external tool to internal vehicle network)
- External test equipment(OEM) should have the vehicle ODX database so it knows the vehicle internal DoIP entities logical address.
- DoIP edge node could act as internal on-board diagnostic tester (e.g. request identification from other internal DoIP nodes, UDS request to collect diagnostic data during operation,...), receive external tool diagnostic request, validate before sending it to target DoIP entity in side vehicle
*The setup of internal vehicle network and edge node behavior for routing diagnostic request varies depend on OEM specification
